recent_25_results.question: 1.6 Where are variables declared in a C++ program?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.6 They can be declared right before they are used, but it is a good practice to declare them at the beginning of the program and label what they are food.

recent_25_results.question: 1.6 Where are variables declared in a C++ program?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.6 In the Function main() before using the variable.

recent_25_results.question: 1.6 Where are variables declared in a C++ program?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.6 Local variables are declared inside the method or function they will be used in at the beginning of the method. Global variables are declared outside of any function or method, generally before functions are defined.

recent_25_results.question: 1.6 Where are variables declared in a C++ program?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.6 Variables are declared where ever it is defined either inside a block locally or outside a block globally.

recent_25_results.question: 1.6 Where are variables declared in a C++ program?
recent_25_results.student_answer: 1.6 Variables are declared before they are actually used. They can be declared before main() to use globally
